thread.title: Grain and livestock mostly lower

title: Grain and livestock mostly lower
text:
Wed, Sep 2, 2015, 5:57 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 4 hrs 3 mins Grain and livestock mostly lower Wheat mixed, corn, oats and soybeans lower on the CBOT; beef lower, pork mixed on the CME. Associated Press – 27 minutes ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were mostly lower Tuesday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for December delivery was up 1.25 cents to $4.8625 a bushel; December corn fell 6.25 cents to 3.69 a bushel; December oats were off 6.25 cents to 2.24 a bushel; while November soybeans lost 13.5 cents to $8.74 a bushel. 
Beef fell while pork was mixed on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. October live cattle was off 1.88 cents to $1.4132 a pound; October feeder cattle lost 2.55 cents to $1.9532 a pound; while October lean hogs fell .05 cent to $.6797 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Qantas lifts passenger numbers in July AAP
